### The Full Mental Model

Here's how all the pieces connect:
```
Unity Editor (what you see)
│
├── Normal Scene
│   ├── Main Camera          ← regular GameObject, stays as-is
│   └── Directional Light    ← regular GameObject, stays as-is
│
└── Sub-Scene "GameWorld"    ← gets BAKED into entities at runtime
    ├── CommandBuilding      → bakes into Entity with CommandBuildingTag + HealthComponent
    ├── Spawner_North        → bakes into Entity with SpawnerComponent
    └── (enemies are         → created at runtime by SpawnerSystem from the prefab)
        spawned at runtime)

Runtime (what actually runs)
│
├── EntityManager            ← owns all entities, like a giant flat database
├── World                    ← container for EntityManager + all systems
└── Systems (auto-discovered, run in order):
    ├── SpawnerSystem        ← creates enemy entities from pool/prefab
    ├── EnemyMovementSystem  ← moves them (Burst parallel job)
    ├── TargetingSystem      ← finds closest enemy per turret
    ├── TurretRotationSystem ← rotates mounts
    └── HealthSystem         ← pools dead enemies, destroys dead turrets